node.accessibility_caption:
Piotr Van Montagu of Belgium competes in the Men's Individual Archery at the 2020 Tokyo Paralympic Games. 

Having been born without arms and with an impairment to his right leg, Piotr holds the bow with his foot. His love for archery began after watching the Lord of the Rings films in 2015. Undeterred by his physical condition, Piotr is one of the top archers in Belgium.

REUTERS/Molly Darlington
